{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889840014,"sessionID":"ses_284b81d1dffePPqIbsE5oe7vgA","part":{"id":"prt_d7b48776b001v2o1EKphnSdRbl","messageID":"msg_d7b486705001cMM18iPJATLkHF","sessionID":"ses_284b81d1dffePPqIbsE5oe7vgA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7baa35be39cb4bd1b161de96c9f705fd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 为 AgentCube 项目实现 Dify 平台插件集成，允许 Dify 用户通过 AgentCube 的代码解释器功能和 Agent Runtime 能力，在 Dify 工作流中安全执行代码和命令。该集成包含两部分：\n6: \n7: 1. **Dify 插件**：提供 AgentCube 代码解释器工具，支持 Python/JavaScript/TypeScript 代码执行和 Shell 命令执行\n8: 2. **PCAP 分析器示例**：演示如何使用 AgentCube SDK 构建一个完整的 FastAPI 应用，包含代码沙箱集成和 AI 驱动的分析流程\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: ### Dify 插件部分\n13: \n14: **文件结构**：\n15: - `manifest.yaml` - 插件根清单文件\n16: - `provider/agentcube.yaml` - 工具提供者描述符\n17: - `provider/agentcube.py` - 提供者实现类\n18: - `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` - 工具参数模式\n19: - `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` - 工具实现类\n20: - `main.py` - 插件入口点\n21: - `requirements.txt` - Python 依赖\n22: - 文档文件（`GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`）\n23: - 图标资源（`icon.png`, `icon-dark.png`）\n24: \n25: **核心功能**：\n26: - Dify 插件框架集成，使用 `dify-plugin` SDK\n27: - 工具提供者凭证验证机制\n28: - AgentCube 代码解释器工具实现，支持：\n29:   - 代码执行（Python/JavaScript/TypeScript）\n30:   - Shell 命令执行\n31:   - 会话管理和复用\n32:   - 文件上传/下载\n33: - 与 AgentCube Router 和 Workload Manager 的集成\n34: \n35: **技术约束**：\n36: - Python 3.12 运行时\n37: - `dify-plugin` 版本范围：`>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`\n38: - `agentcube-sdk` 版本：`>=0.0.10`\n39: - 最大请求超时：120 秒\n40: \n41: ### PCAP 分析器示例部分\n42: \n43: **文件结构**：\n44: - `pcap_analyzer.py` - FastAPI 应用主文件\n45: - `requirements.txt` - 依赖清单\n46: - `Dockerfile` - 容器镜像构建文件\n47: - `deployment.yaml` - Kubernetes 部署清单\n48: \n49: **核心功能**：\n50: - FastAPI 服务，提供 PCAP 文件分析接口\n51: - 基于 LangChain/LangGraph 的多 Agent 协作：\n52:   - React Agent：代码生成和执行\n53:   - Planner Agent：分析脚本规划\n54:   - Reporter Agent：结果汇总报告\n55: - AgentCube 沙箱集成：\n56:   - 沙箱会话管理（`SandboxRunner`）\n57:   - 文件上传（`upload_file`, `upload_bytes`）\n58:   - 命令执行（`run`）\n59: - 自动脚本修复机制（带重试）\n60: \n61: **技术栈**：\n62: - FastAPI 0.120.0 + Uvicorn 0.38.0\n63: - LangChain 1.0.2 + LangGraph 1.0.1\n64: - OpenAI 兼容 API（默认使用 SiliconFlow）\n65: - AgentCube Python SDK\n66: \n67: ### Python SDK 增强\n68: \n69: 虽然 SDK 已存在，本提案确认以下依赖关系：\n70: \n71: **核心客户端类**：\n72: - `CodeInterpreterClient`：代码解释器会话管理\n73:   - 控制平面：通过 `ControlPlaneClient` 创建/删除会话\n74:   - 数据平面：通过 `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` 执行代码/命令/文件操作\n75: - `AgentRuntimeClient`：Agent Runtime 调用\n76:   - 数据平面：通过 `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` 调用 Agent\n77: \n78: **关键功能**：\n79: - 上下文管理器支持（自动清理）\n80: - 会话 ID 管理和复用\n81: - HTTP 连接池优化\n82: - 异常层次结构（`CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`）\n83: - 超时配置（默认 120 秒读取，5 秒连接）\n84: \n85: ### 不包括在此范围\n86: \n87: - Dify 平台本身的修改\n88: - AgentCube 服务端的实现（Router, Workload Manager, PicoD 等）\n89: - 其他代码解释器语言（仅 Python/JavaScript/TypeScript）\n90: - 插件的多语言本地化（除基础支持外）\n91: \n92: ## Impact Analysis\n93: \n94: ### 影响范围\n95: \n96: **新增组件**：\n97: - Dify 插件包（约 10+ 个文件）\n98: - PCAP 分析器应用（4 个文件）\n99: - 示例和文档\n100: \n101: **依赖关系**：\n102: - Dify 插件框架（`dify-plugin`）\n103: - AgentCube SDK（`agentcube-sdk`）\n104: - AgentCube 服务基础设施（Router, Workload Manager）\n105: \n106: **集成点**：\n107: 1. Dify 平台 ↔ AgentCube Router（通过插件）\n108: 2. Dify 工作流 ↔ 代码解释器沙箱（通过 SDK）\n109: 3. PCAP 分析器 ↔ AgentCube Agent Runtime（可选）\n110: \n111: ### 性能考虑\n112: \n113: **插件性能**：\n114: - 最大请求超时限制为 120 秒，防止长时间运行的代码阻塞 Dify\n115: - HTTP 连接池复用（默认 10 连接）\n116: - 会话复用机制（`session_reuse` 参数）减少会话创建开销\n117: \n118: **示例应用性能**：\n119: - 沙箱预热配置（`SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` 默认 5 秒）\n120: - LLM API 调用链路（Planner → React Agent → Reporter）\n121: - 资源请求：200m CPU / 100Mi 内存\n122: - 资源限制：1 CPU / 1Gi 内存\n123: \n124: ### 安全考虑\n125: \n126: **凭证验证**：\n127: - 工具提供者实现 `_validate_credentials` 方法\n128: - 使用 Dify 的 `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` 传播验证失败\n129: \n130: **会话管理**：\n131: - 支持服务账号令牌（从 K8s Secret 读取）\n132: - 会话 TTL 配置（默认 3600 秒）\n133: - 上下文管理器自动清理会话\n134: \n135: **文件操作**：\n136: - 仅限插件配置的沙箱命名空间\n137: - 文件权限设置为 0644\n138: \n139: ### 兼容性\n140: \n141: **Dify 兼容性**：\n142: - 遵循 Dify 插件清单规范\n143: - 支持多语言标签（en_US, ja_JP, zh_Hans, pt_BR）\n144: - 资源声明（memory, permission flags）\n145: \n146: **平台兼容性**：\n147: - Python 3.12\n148: - Linux（amd64, arm64）\n149: - Kubernetes（用于 PCAP 分析器部署）\n150: \n151: **LLM 兼容性**：\n152: - OpenAI 兼容 API\n153: - 示例使用 SiliconFlow Qwen/QwQ-32B\n154: \n155: ## Alternatives Considered\n156: \n157: ### 方案 A：仅 SDK 集成，不提供 Dify 插件\n158: \n159: **优点**：\n160: - 更轻量，不依赖 Dify 插件框架\n161: - 更灵活，可用于任何 Python 应用\n162: \n163: **缺点**：\n164: - Dify 用户无法直接使用 AgentCube 能力\n165: - 需要用户自己编写集成代码\n166: - 降低 AgentCube 的可发现性\n167: \n168: **结论**：不采用。Dify 是主要目标平台，必须提供插件。\n169: \n170: ### 方案 B：使用多插件架构（代码解释器 + Agent Runtime 作为独立工具）\n171: \n172: **优点**：\n173: - 更细粒度的控制\n174: - 可以独立更新每个工具\n175: \n176: **缺点**：\n177: - 增加维护复杂度\n178: - 两个工具共享相同的凭证验证逻辑\n179: - 可能造成用户困惑\n180: \n181: **结论**：不采用。当前设计将代码解释器作为主要工具，Agent Runtime 可通过 SDK 直接使用，减少复杂度。\n182: \n183: ### 方案 C：PCAP 分析器使用纯函数式设计（无 Agent）\n184: \n185: **优点**：\n186: - 更简单的代码结构\n187: - 更少的 LLM 调用（成本更低）\n188: \n189: **缺点**：\n190: - 缺乏自动化脚本修复能力\n191: - 分析报告质量依赖预定义逻辑\n192: - 无法展示 SDK 的完整能力\n193: \n194: **结论**：不采用。多 Agent 设计展示了 SDK 与 AI 工作流集成的最佳实践。\n195: \n196: ### 方案 D：插件使用 OAuth 认证而非简单 URL 配置\n197: \n198: **优点**：\n199: - 更安全的凭证管理\n200: - 符合现代认证标准\n201: \n202: **缺点**：\n203: - 增加集成复杂度\n204: - AgentCube 当前不提供 OAuth 端点\n205: - 可能需要额外的基础设施\n206: \n207: **结论**：当前设计保留 OAuth 注释作为未来扩展选项，初始版本使用 URL + 令牌认证。\n208: \n209: ## Implementation Plan\n210: \n211: ### 阶段 1：Dify 插件核心实现\n212: \n213: 1. 创建插件目录结构\n214: 2. 实现 `manifest.yaml`\n215: 3. 实现 `provider/agentcube.yaml` 和 `provider/agentcube.py`\n216: 4. 实现 `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` 和 `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n217: 5. 实现 `main.py` 入口点\n218: 6. 添加 `requirements.txt`\n219: 7. 基础测试和验证\n220: \n221: ### 阶段 2：插件文档和打包\n222: \n223: 1. 编写 `README.md`\n224: 2. 编写 `GUIDE.md`（使用指南）\n225: 3. 编写 `PRIVACY.md`\n226: 4. 添加图标资源\n227: 5. 测试 Dify 平台加载和执行\n228: \n229: ### 阶段 3：PCAP 分析器实现\n230: \n231: 1. 实现 `SandboxRunner` 类\n232: 2. 实现 LangChain/LangGraph Agent 构建\n233: 3. 实现 FastAPI 应用和 `/analyze` 端点\n234: 4. 实现脚本规划和修复逻辑\n235: 5. 添加 `requirements.txt`\n236: \n237: ### 阶段 4：容器化和部署\n238: \n239: 1. 编写 `Dockerfile`\n240: 2. 编写 `deployment.yaml`\n241: 3. 本地容器测试\n242: 4. Kubernetes 部署测试\n243: \n244: ### 阶段 5：集成测试和文档\n245: \n246: 1. 端到端测试（Dify 插件 + AgentCube 服务）\n247: 2. PCAP 分析器功能测试\n248: 3. 完善文档\n249: 4. 示例代码验证\n250: \n251: ## Success Criteria\n252: \n253: 1. Dify 插件可成功加载和配置\n254: 2. 插件工具可正确执行代码和命令\n255: 3. 凭证验证机制正常工作\n256: 4. 会话复用功能正常工作\n257: 5. PCAP 分析器可成功部署到 Kubernetes\n258: 6. PCAP 分析器可分析实际 PCAP 文件并生成报告\n259: 7. 所有示例代码可运行并通过测试\n260: 8. 文档完整且准确\n261: \n262: ## Open Questions\n263: \n264: 1. Dify 插件的分发机制是什么？（直接提供 ZIP 包或使用插件市场）\n265: 2. AgentCube Router 和 Workload Manager 的部署模型是什么？（本地、云端、混合）\n266: 3. 是否需要支持代码解释器的并发限制？\n267: 4. PCAP 分析器示例的 LLM 模型选择是否需要可配置？\n\n(End of file - total 267 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 AgentCube 项目实现 Dify 平台插件集成，允许 Dify 用户通过 AgentCube 的代码解释器功能和 Agent Runtime 能力，在 Dify 工作流中安全执行代码和命令。该集成包含两部分：\n\n1. **Dify 插件**：提供 AgentCube 代码解释器工具，支持 Python/JavaScript/TypeScript 代码执行和 Shell 命令执行\n2. **PCAP 分析器示例**：演示如何使用 AgentCube SDK 构建一个完整的 FastAPI 应用，包含代码沙箱集成和 AI 驱动的分析流程\n\n## Scope\n\n### Dify 插件部分\n\n**文件结构**：\n- `manifest.yaml` - 插件根清单文件\n- `provider/agentcube.yaml` - 工具提供者描述符\n- `provider/agentcube.py` - 提供者实现类\n- `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` - 工具参数模式\n- `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` - 工具实现类\n- `main.py` - 插件入口点","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775889840002,"end":1775889840011}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775889840039,"sessionID":"ses_284b81d1dffePPqIbsE5oe7vgA","part":{"id":"prt_d7b48778d001cK7GRxvgFtAHIt","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b486705001cMM18iPJATLkHF","sessionID":"ses_284b81d1dffePPqIbsE5oe7vgA","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":23744,"input":8631,"output":74,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15039}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775889841965,"sessionID":"ses_284b81d1dffePPqIbsE5oe7vgA","part":{"id":"prt_d7b487f2a001ZkCV9WQggm8yIb","messageID":"msg_d7b4877c1001QA4yqwUBhlt4YV","sessionID":"ses_284b81d1dffePPqIbsE5oe7vgA","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889872129,"sessionID":"ses_284b81d1dffePPqIbsE5oe7vgA","part":{"id":"prt_d7b48f4be001QaDckHCs529hVC","messageID":"msg_d7b4877c1001QA4yqwUBhlt4YV","sessionID":"ses_284b81d1dffePPqIbsE5oe7vgA","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-b59ab550418e4d9ab0c635974208a33c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: PCAP Analyzer Example Application\n\n**AR:** AR-037\n**Module:** example\n**Language:** Python\n**Size:** M\n\n## Purpose\n\nCreate a comprehensive PCAP (Packet Capture) analyzer example application that demonstrates the capabilities of the AgentCube Python SDK. This example will showcase how to use the `CodeInterpreterClient` to process network packet captures, analyze traffic patterns, extract meaningful insights, and perform forensic analysis tasks.\n\nThe PCAP analyzer will serve as both a practical tool for network analysis and an educational resource for developers learning to use the AgentCube SDK, particularly demonstrating:\n\n- Remote code execution capabilities through `CodeInterpreterClient`\n- File upload/download workflows for large datasets\n- Session management and lifecycle\n- Error handling and recovery patterns\n- Integration with Python network analysis libraries\n\n## Scope\n\n### Core Functionality\n\nThe PCAP analyzer example will provide the following features:\n\n1. **PCAP File Processing**\n   - Upload PCAP files to the remote Code Interpreter session\n   - Parse PCAP files using `scapy` or `pyshark` libraries\n   - Extract packet-level metadata (timestamps, protocols, source/destination IPs, ports)\n\n2. **Traffic Analysis**\n   - Protocol distribution analysis (HTTP, HTTPS, DNS, TCP, UDP, etc.)\n   - Top source and destination IP addresses by packet count and bytes\n   - Port frequency analysis\n   - Time-based traffic patterns and anomalies detection\n\n3. **Advanced Analysis**\n   - DNS query/response pattern extraction\n   - HTTP/HTTPS header and payload analysis\n   - TCP stream reassembly for specific conversations\n   - Statistical summaries (packet rates, average packet sizes, etc.)\n\n4. **Reporting and Visualization**\n   - Generate comprehensive text reports\n   - Create simple ASCII-based visualizations for traffic distribution\n   - Export results to CSV/JSON formats\n\n### Implementation Approach\n\nThe example will be structured as a Python script that:\n\n1. Uses `CodeInterpreterClient` as a context manager for proper session lifecycle\n2. Demonstrates error handling with `CommandExecutionError` and other SDK exceptions\n3. Implements modular analysis functions that can be composed\n4. Includes comprehensive docstrings and inline comments\n5. Provides CLI arguments for flexible usage (input file, output format, analysis type)\n\n### Technical Requirements\n\n- **Python Version:** 3.10+\n- **Dependencies:** \n  - `agentcube-sdk` (from the Python SDK)\n  - `scapy` or `pyshark` for PCAP parsing\n  - Standard library: `argparse`, `json`, `csv`, `collections`, `datetime`\n- **Configuration:**\n  - `ROUTER_URL` environment variable or command-line argument\n  - Optional `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` for session management\n  - Optional `auth_token` for authentication\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Positive Impacts\n\n1. **SDK Demonstration Value**\n   - Provides a realistic, complex use case that showcases SDK capabilities\n   - Demonstrates best practices for session management, error handling, and resource cleanup\n   - Shows integration patterns with third-party Python libraries\n\n2. **User Onboarding**\n   - New users can see a complete, working example beyond simple \"hello world\"\n   - Illustrates how to handle file I/O operations through the SDK\n   - Shows patterns for long-running analysis tasks\n\n3. **Documentation and Testing**\n   - Serves as integration test material for the SDK\n   - Provides real-world scenarios for SDK documentation\n   - Can be used to validate SDK functionality during development\n\n4. **Community Engagement**\n   - Network security practitioners may find practical value\n   - Encourages contributions of additional analysis modules\n   - Demonstrates the SDK's applicability to data-intensive tasks\n\n### Potential Risks and Mitigations\n\n1. **Resource Consumption**\n   - **Risk:** Large PCAP files may consume significant memory/CPU in remote sessions\n   - **Mitigation:** Implement file size checks and progress indicators; recommend session configuration adjustments for large files\n\n2. **Library Availability**\n   - **Risk:** Analysis libraries (`scapy`, `pyshark`) may not be pre-installed in remote environments\n   - **Mitigation:** Document installation requirements; include fallback logic or error messages; provide setup instructions\n\n3. **Session Timeouts**\n   - **Risk:** Long-running analysis may exceed default TTL (3600s)\n   - **Risk:** Analysis may exceed `timeout=120` default for individual operations\n   - **Mitigation:** Demonstrate TTL configuration; show per-call timeout overrides; implement checkpoint/restart patterns\n\n4. **Complexity Management**\n   - **Risk:** Example may become too complex for new users\n   - **Mitigation:** Provide modular design with clear separation of concerns; include simplified usage examples; structure code with progressive complexity\n\n### Dependencies on Other Components\n\n1. **AgentCube Python SDK**\n   - Requires stable `CodeInterpreterClient` API\n   - Depends on file upload/download reliability\n   - Assumes session management functionality works as specified\n\n2. **Remote Environment**\n   - Requires network analysis libraries to be available\n   - Assumes sufficient memory/CPU for PCAP processing\n   - Needs persistent storage for intermediate files (if needed)\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Simple Command Example\n**Description:** Create a minimal example that only executes a single PCAP analysis command.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Simpler to understand and maintain\n- Faster to implement\n- Lower resource requirements\n\n**Cons:**\n- Doesn't demonstrate full SDK capabilities\n- Less valuable for real-world use cases\n- Limited educational value\n\n**Decision:** Rejected in favor of comprehensive example that provides more value.\n\n### Alternative 2: Web Application Interface\n**Description:** Build a Flask/FastAPI web application that uses the SDK for PCAP analysis.\n\n**Pros:**\n- More user-friendly interface\n- Could demonstrate `AgentRuntimeClient` integration\n- Potential for interactive analysis\n\n**Cons:**\n- Introduces additional complexity (web framework, frontend)\n- Shiftes focus away from SDK demonstration\n- Requires additional infrastructure considerations\n\n**Decision:** Deferred; CLI-based example better focuses on SDK usage patterns.\n\n### Alternative 3: Multiple Small Examples\n**Description:** Create several focused examples (e.g., upload-example.py, analysis-example.py, download-example.py).\n\n**Pros:**\n- Easier to understand individual concepts\n- Modular and composable\n- Lower barrier to entry\n\n**Cons:**\n- Doesn't show integration of multiple SDK features\n- Users must piece together patterns themselves\n- More files to maintain and document\n\n**Decision:** Partially adopted - will create comprehensive main example but structure code with modular functions that can serve as focused examples.\n\n### Alternative 4: Language-agnostic Example\n**Description:** Create examples in multiple languages (Python, Go, Java) to demonstrate multi-language SDK support.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Shows SDK versatility\n- Reaches broader developer audience\n- Demonstrates consistent design across languages\n\n**Cons:**\n- Significant implementation overhead\n- Maintenance burden increases\n- Python SDK naturally suited for Python examples\n\n**Decision:** Focus on Python initially; other language examples can be added later based on demand.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1)\n- Create basic project structure and CLI argument parsing\n- Implement PCAP file upload to Code Interpreter session\n- Add basic PCAP parsing functionality with `scapy`\n- Create simple analysis: packet count and protocol distribution\n\n### Phase 2: Core Analysis (Week 2)\n- Implement IP address frequency analysis\n- Add port analysis functionality\n- Create time-based traffic pattern detection\n- Develop statistical summary generation\n\n### Phase 3: Advanced Features (Week 3)\n- Add DNS query/response extraction\n- Implement HTTP header analysis\n- Create TCP stream reassembly for selected conversations\n- Develop report generation (text, CSV, JSON formats)\n\n### Phase 4: Polish and Documentation (Week 4)\n- Add comprehensive error handling and recovery logic\n- Implement progress indicators for long operations\n- Create detailed README with usage examples\n- Add inline documentation and docstrings\n- Test with various PCAP file sizes and types\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. **Functional Completeness**\n   - All planned analysis features work correctly\n   - Handles PCAP files from 1MB to 1GB\n   - Generates accurate and useful reports\n\n2. **SDK Demonstration**\n   - Uses at least 80% of `CodeInterpreterClient` public API\n   - Demonstrates proper context manager usage\n   - Shows effective error handling patterns\n\n3. **Code Quality**\n   - Follows Python PEP 8 style guidelines\n   - Comprehensive test coverage (>70%)\n   - Clear, maintainable code structure\n\n4. **Documentation**\n   - README with installation and usage instructions\n   - Inline comments explaining SDK integration\n   - Example outputs for different analysis types\n\n5. **User Experience**\n   - CLI provides helpful error messages\n   - Progress indicators for long operations\n   - Flexible configuration options\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe PCAP analyzer example application will provide significant value to the AgentCube project by demonstrating practical SDK usage patterns in a realistic scenario. While implementation requires careful attention to resource management and error handling, the resulting example will serve as an excellent resource for both SDK users and developers.\n\nThe comprehensive approach balances demonstrating SDK capabilities with maintaining approachability for new users, making it an ideal addition to the examples module.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775889872086,"end":1775889872127}}}}
